<TEXT>
laurence beilenson who helped found the 
screen actors guild and other hollywood unions in the 1930s as well 
as serving such clients as thenactor ronald reagan died monday of 
a stroke he was 89 
beilenson helped to found or organize the original screen 
writers guild the screen actors guild the directors guild of 
america and the american federation of television amp radio artists 
the writers guild later became the writers guild of america 
beilenson was a staff lawyer with sag from its start in 1933 
helped negotiate sags first contract with film producers in 1937 
and stayed on as counsel until 1949 his show business clients 
ranged from reagan to greta garbo to groucho marx after retiring 
from sag he served as legal counsel to mca artists ltd and wrote 
three books the treaty trap power through subversion and 
survival and peace in the nuclear age 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
bill roberts 63 a veteran 
political manager who engineered president reagans early campaign 
triumphs and a major figure in california republican politics for 
more than three decades died thursday 
among hundreds of california campaigns managed by roberts 
either independently or with longtime colleague stu spencer were 
reagans successful campaigns for governor in 1966 and 1970 and 
george deukmejians gubernatorial campaign in 1982 
the most recent statewide campaign managed by roberts was the 
successful drive in 1986 to remove chief justice rose bird and 
justices joseph grodin and cruz reynoso from the california supreme 
court 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
robert o fishel american league executive vice 
president and majorleague executive for more than 40 years died 
thursday apparently of a heart attack at age 74 
fishel began his connection with baseball as an advertising 
executive handling the indians radio network account for a local 
agency in 1951 he was named publicity director of the st louis 
browns by owner bill veeck who had owned the indians during 
fishels time in cleveland 
fishel joined the yankees as publicity director in 1954 and 
served with them for 20 years he rose to a vicepresidency before 
joining the american league in 1974 as a special assistant to al 
president lee macphail his former boss with the yankees four 
years later fishel was voted league secretary and was elected 
executive vice president in 1983 
</TEXT>
