a nicaraguan businessman have been sentenced for passing economic 
secrets to the united states news reports said 
the progovernment nuevo diario newspaper said thursday that 
nora aldana centeno a former planning official and mario jose 
alegria castillo an official of the superior council of private 
enterprise were sentenced wednesday to 16 years for passing secret 
economic documents to us embassy officials 
they were arrested in late may and were accused of taking 
documents with the classification secret the paper said 
alegria castillo director of the councils institute of 
economic and social research also was charged with organizing a 
network of informants in some nicaraguan state institutions it 
added 
pedro su olivas a central bank official and adrian espinales 
