<TEXT>
more than one million children in china 
officially do not exist because they were born outside state birth 
control targets rendering them unable to receive food rations 
schooling and job assignments an official report said 
the children most of whom are under age 10 are commonly 
referred to as black children they are children whose parents 
did not have their births registered or who were refused 
registration by local authorities the peoples daily reported 
thursday 
under chinas onechild policy officials in each county are 
responsible for ensuring that each woman has only one child and 
that the number of births in the county does not exceed the birth 
target set by the state 
parents are penalized for having more than one child and 
officials are penalized if the county goes over the number of 
births that it is allowed officials however are financially 
rewarded if births stay within the target 
some parents did not register births of their second or 
subsequent children to avoid paying the fine the paper said fines 
vary from region to region but are generally 270 or more per year 
for five years a huge fine by chinese standards 
some local officials seeing their bonuses jeapordized by too 
many births simply refuse to register new babies the paper said 
in one city in southwestern chinas sichuan province local 
officials refused to register the births of 450 babies because the 
birth target had already been reached the report said 
without a residence permit children are deprived of the rights 
of a chinese citizen they do not receive their ration of rice and 
edible oil are unable to register for school and will not be able 
to get a job join the military or sit for college entrance exams 
when they grow up the newspaper said 
the problem will become even greater when these children marry 
and have children of their own who also will be unable to get 
residence permits it said 
the situation is most serious in the provinces of hebei 
shandong jiangxi and guizhou in each of these provinces black 
children number more than 70000 the report said 
state officials have called attention to the problem saying 
that the children are innocent victims the newspaper reported 
they said the situation not only hurts the children it also 
affects the nations family planning and population control efforts 
and creates social problems 
chinas birth rate hit 2 percent in 1986 and stayed there last 
year if the trend continues chinas population of 108 billion 
will double by the year 2030 according to the united nations fund 
for population activities 
china has said that it must keep the birth rate at 15 percent 
if it is to meet its goal of keeping the population under 12 
billion by the year 2000 
china will mark asias three billion population day today in a 
televised speech for the occasion chinese premier li peng said 
thursday the country has listed family planning as one of its 
basic national policies and taken the control of population growth 
as a strategic task 
