<TEXT>
a world war ii veteran plans to fly solo across 
the atlantic to return to the german battlefield where a snipers 
bullet left him a paraplegic 43 years ago and west german 
officials are waiting to honor him 
clark harrison 63 a real estate company owner and bank 
chairman in suburban decatur took off at about 930 am today 
from dekalbpeachtree airport in a singleengine cherokee piper 
equipped with hand controls and an extra gas tank 
what scares me the most is rolling around in this wheelchair 
and getting in and out of it he said the easy part is the 
flying once i get on the ground thats the hard part 
the residents of stolberg west germany will be celebrating 
what city manager heinrich romer called harrisons spirit of 
enterprise and courage as he completes a 4669mile solo 
transatlantic flight via greenland and great britain 
the reception at stolbergs historic castle is scheduled for 
july 11 the day harrison hopes weather permitting to arrive at 
the nearby airport in aachen west germany 
harrison flies in a cramped twoseat cockpit filled with his 
wheelchair his luggage a life raft survival kit and an auxiliary 
fuel tank he gets in and out of the plane by crawling onto the 
wing which sits about three feet off the ground and then pulling 
the wheelchair up or letting it down with a strap 
harrison a founding director of the shepherd spinal center in 
atlanta hopes his trip will raise enough money for a center for 
independent living at the hospital to help the newly paralyzed 
learn to care for themselves 
supporters are pledging to the hospital up to 1 for each of the 
4669 miles he plans to cover 
harrison who has already flown solo to alaska and back says 
flying alone has great attraction for someone for whom more routine 
tasks can be difficult 
when i was a kid and i first got shot harrison said 
recalling his days as a 20yearold infantryman i was in a 
hospital for a year and a half they didnt know what to do with 
us we were just invalids when that happens when youre young you 
miss out on a lot so when you have a chance to transport yourself 
over great distances it has a lot of appeal 
