its anticollision strobe turned on as required at the time of the 
march 8 accident 
the report also cited other factors including limited pilot 
training using nightvision goggles and exterior and interior 
design flaws of the black hawk 
the report said there was no evidence of a mechanical 
malfunction 
there should be no action taken against anyone as no 
foundation for negligence can be established the report said 
the accident was not due to lack of diligence nor unreasonable 
or unprofessional conduct 
