the television documentary much neglected in 
recent years gets a special 10week showcase on public television 
beginning tonight 
the summer series pov filmmaker jargon for point of 
view will present a selection from among the best documentaries 
produced in recent years by independent filmmakers 
each film has a point of view said executive producer marc 
n weiss that makes them more interesting people can look at 
them and agree or disagree 
the first twohour program presents two documentaries 
american tongues by louis alvarez and andrew kolker takes a 
humorous look at how american speech varies from region to region 
the film won a peabody award this spring the second film is 
