<TEXT>
egypts decision to cut the price on its crude 
oil exports for the first half of july has raised prospects of a 
possible price war depressing oil futures prices to their lowest 
levels of the year 
the contract for august delivery of west texas intermediate the 
benchmark us crude oil dropped 27 cents thursday to 1516 per 
barrel on the new york mercantile exchange 
it was the lowest level for wti since dec 21 1987 when the 
nearterm contract also finished at 1516 
among refined products traded on the exchange the july contract 
for home heating oil slipped 064 cent to 4088 cents a gallon 
the july contract for unleaded gasoline settled at 5194 cents 
down 068 cent from the previous strong session when prices soared 
on speculation that demand would grow as the july 4th holiday 
neared traders attributed thursdays decline largely to 
profittaking 
john oconnell a senior analyst for refco inc said egypts 
announcement made traders even more bearish about the outlook for 
oil prices than they had been in recent weeks 
traders have been worried about overproduction by oil nations 
who have created a glut that has been depressing prices 
egypts senior oil ministry official hammad ayoub said his 
country would reduce its oil export prices by up to 185 a barrel 
for the first half of july 
ayoub declined to comment further but in a later interview with 
the middle east news agency he blamed the deterioration in world 
oil prices on some opec countries that are exceeding the production 
quotas agreed to by all but one of the cartels 13 members 
oconnell said the action by egypt which is not a member of the 
organization of petroleum exporting countries could prompt some 
opec countries to increase their production to remain competitive 
the oil futures market is nervous about what kuwait and 
saudi arabia might do if other opec members cheated further on 
their quotas oconnell said 
ayoub did not mention any opec countries by name but said that 
all countries should remain committed to their quotas and stay 
away from unclear selling tactics 
