more than 10000 submarine builders at the 
electric boat shipyard went on strike today after refusing to 
accept the companys offer of lumpsum bonuses instead of wage 
increases over the next three years 
the metal trades council representing more than half of the 
shipyards 18000 workers negotiated with the company until a half 
hour before the midnight deadline before announcing an impasse 
no new talks were planned union and company officials said 
early today 
about 300 chanting pickets marched outside the gates of the 
giant yard under sunny skies this morning city police reported two 
arrests one of a man setting off fireworks and another of a man 
who allegedly drove his car through police barricades in front of 
